  <RimTalk_Preview_HelpContent>=== Injection Previewer Help ===

【Overview】
This tool previews memory and knowledge injection effects, helping you understand what information will be used during AI conversations.

【Knowledge Injection】
• Matching Sources: Select variables used for knowledge matching
• Pawn property variables will parse all participants
• Parsed match text is used to keyword-match against the knowledge library
• Match results are sorted by score

【Memory Injection】
• ABM: Ultra short-term dialogue memory
• SCM: Short-term memory (deprecated, now summarizes to ELS)
• ELS: Event Log Storage (AI-summarized memories)
• CLPA: Long-term Archive (important event archives)

【How to Use】
1. Select current pawn (required)
2. Optional: Select target pawn (simulates conversation)
3. Check the matching sources you need
4. Click "Refresh Preview" to see results

【Tips】
• Matching source settings sync to global settings
• Pawn property variables only need pawn info to parse
• Environment variables require map information
• Other variables require at least one generated conversation to parse
</RimTalk_Preview_HelpContent>
